text.tspan: Timeline of Writing Systems’ Graphical Evolution
Chinese: Scripts derived from Oracle Bone
Southern Brahmi: Scripts derived from Brahmi in South India
Northern Brahmi: Scripts derived from Brahmi in North India
文 Logograph: Words are distinct characters
か Syllabary: Syllables are distinct characters
Ω True alphabet: Vowels are on par with consonants
گ दे Ω Alphabets: Consonants are distinct characters
दे Abugida: Vowels are secondary, usually diacritics
گ Abjad: Vowels are optional or non-existant
